.TH "t4vf_set_addr_hash" 9 "t4vf_set_addr_hash" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
t4vf_set_addr_hash \- program the MAC inexact-match hash filter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" t4vf_set_addr_hash
.BI "(struct adapter *adapter "  ","
.BI "unsigned int viid "  ","
.BI "bool ucast "  ","
.BI "u64 vec "  ","
.BI "bool sleep_ok "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "adapter" 12
the adapter
.IP "viid" 12
the Virtual Interface Identifier
.IP "ucast" 12
whether the hash filter should also match unicast addresses
.IP "vec" 12
the value to be written to the hash filter
.IP "sleep_ok" 12
call is allowed to sleep

Sets the 64-bit inexact-match hash filter for a virtual interface.
